&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Radiologists &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Isle of Wight NHS Trust&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;10 Programmed Activities&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Consultant Radiologists at St Mary’s Hospital on the Isle of Wight to join a team of five.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is happy to consider flexible working in support of work / life balance. Extended days and compressed hours will be considered as well as weekend sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates will be General Radiologist with a special interest in Musculoskeletal Radiology, Oncology or Cross-Sectional Imaging. However, we are flexible and would not discount or discourage any interested candidate, with a view to developing their specialty interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The philosophy of the department is to provide a comprehensive, modern Radiology service including CT, MRI, Plain Radiography, Ultrasound and basic interventional procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key features of the jobs are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• No on-call&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 10 PAs per week +1 PA extra by mutual agreement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• The 10 PAs can be compressed into four/ three longer days to help deliver more flexible working patterns and provide a desirable work/ life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Small friendly dynamic department where you feel valued with high levels of job satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Relocation/retention package is on offer to suitable candidates. Assistance with initial accommodation will also be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Dr Stephan Voigt, Lead Clinician on 01983 534636, email stephan.voigt@iow.nhs.uk or Andy Stant, Deputy Head of Diagnostic Imaging on 01983 534669, email andrew.stant@iow.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*The Trust is planning for an AAC to be take place week commencing 31st August*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
